\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left(-\Delta+1\right)u+\sigma\left|u\right|^{2p}u=0.\label{eq:profile}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Consider 
\begin_inset Formula $R=E^{-\frac{1}{2}}$
\end_inset

.
 Under certain decay conditions on the potential 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|x\right|\to\infty$
\end_inset

 
