\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $R\left(\theta\right)=\begin{pmatrix}\cos\theta & -\sin\theta\\
\sin\theta & \cos\theta
\end{pmatrix}$
\end_inset

 be the 2-dimensional rotation matrix with inverse 
\begin_inset Formula $R^{-1}\left(\theta\right)=\begin{pmatrix}\cos\theta & \sin\theta\\
-\sin\theta & \cos\theta
\end{pmatrix}$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{1},y_{2},y_{3}$
\end_inset

 denote the connected,
 coplanar,
 points lying in the plane spanned by vectors 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{r_{1}},\boldsymbol{r_{2}}\in\mathbb{R}^{2}$
